theorem Topology.dense_interior_iff_closure_interior_eq_univ {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior (A : Set X)) ‚Üî
      closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
  constructor
  ¬∑ intro hDense
    exact
      Topology.closure_interior_eq_univ_of_dense_interior (A := A) hDense
  ¬∑ intro hEq
    exact ‚ü®hEq‚ü©

theorem Topology.P3_iff_forall_open_nbhd_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P3 A ‚Üî
      ‚àÄ x : X, x ‚àà (A : Set X) ‚Üí
        ‚àÉ U : Set X, IsOpen U ‚àß x ‚àà U ‚àß U ‚äÜ closure (A : Set X) := by
  constructor
  ¬∑ intro hP3 x hxA
    -- From `P3`, obtain that `x` is in the interior of `closure A`.
    have hx_int : x ‚àà interior (closure (A : Set X)) := hP3 hxA
    -- Unpack the definition of `interior`.
    rcases mem_interior.1 hx_int with ‚ü®U, hU_open, hxU, hU_sub‚ü©
    exact ‚ü®U, hU_open, hxU, hU_sub‚ü©
  ¬∑ intro h x hxA
    -- Obtain an open neighbourhood of `x` contained in `closure A`.
    rcases h x hxA with ‚ü®U, hU_open, hxU, hU_sub‚ü©
    -- Turn this neighbourhood into the required interior membership.
    have hxInt : x ‚àà interior (closure (A : Set X)) := by
      -- `U` is a neighbourhood of `x`.
      have hU_nhds : (U : Set X) ‚àà ùìù x := hU_open.mem_nhds hxU
      -- Since `U ‚äÜ closure A`, `closure A` is also a neighbourhood of `x`.
      have hCl_nhds : (closure (A : Set X)) ‚àà ùìù x :=
        Filter.mem_of_superset hU_nhds hU_sub
      -- Use the neighbourhood characterisation of the interior.
      exact (mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds).2 hCl_nhds
    exact hxInt

theorem Topology.interior_union_of_isOpen {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) (hB : IsOpen (B : Set X)) :
    interior (A ‚à™ B : Set X) = interior A ‚à™ interior B := by
  -- Evaluate the interiors of the open sets `A` and `B`.
  have hIntA : interior A = A := hA.interior_eq
  have hIntB : interior B = B := hB.interior_eq
  -- The union of two open sets is open, so its interior is itself.
  have hIntUnion : interior (A ‚à™ B : Set X) = A ‚à™ B :=
    (hA.union hB).interior_eq
  -- Rewrite everything using the computed equalities.
  simpa [hIntA, hIntB, hIntUnion]
